# Project Helpers

## Site Details Anchor

When building a URL that links to a specific site card on the review-site-details page, use `getSiteDetailsAnchor` rather than constructing the anchor string manually.

```javascript
import { getSiteDetailsAnchor } from '#src/server/common/helpers/site-details/anchor-utils.js'

// siteNumber is 1-based (the display number)
const url = `${marineLicenceRoutes.MARINE_LICENCE_REVIEW_SITE_DETAILS}${getSiteDetailsAnchor(siteNumber)}`

// If you only have siteIndex (0-based), convert first
const url = `${marineLicenceRoutes.MARINE_LICENCE_REVIEW_SITE_DETAILS}${getSiteDetailsAnchor(siteIndex + 1)}`
```

- Location: `src/server/common/helpers/site-details/anchor-utils.js`
- The anchor matches the `id: "site-details-" + site.siteNumber` set on site cards in the review-site-details Nunjucks templates.
